#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn2.25"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.25:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.25:0.2"
msgid "3. Nānātitthiyavagga "
msgstr "3. Various Sectarians "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.25:0.3"
msgid "25. Jantusutta "
msgstr "25. With Jantu "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.61, sc1
msgctxt "sn2.25:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span></p><p>
# NOTE: Surely the fact that several mendicants are staying there suggests that kutika doesn’t mean “little” hut?
msgctxt "sn2.25:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā bhikkhū, kosalesu viharanti himavantapasse araññakuṭikāya uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā vibbhantacittā pākatindriyā. "
msgstr "Now at that time several mendicants were staying in the Kosalan lands, in a wilderness hut on the slopes of the Himalayas. They were restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, loose-tongued, unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with straying minds and undisciplined faculties. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn2.25:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho jantu devaputto tadahuposathe pannarase yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then on the fifteenth day sabbath the god Jantu went up to those mendicants and addressed them in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn2.25:3.1"
msgid "“Sukhajīvino pure āsuṃ, "
msgstr "“The mendicants used to live happily, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:3.2"
msgid "bhikkhū gotamasāvakā; "
msgstr "as disciples of Gotama. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: piṇḍamesanā → piṇḍamesānā (pts2)
msgctxt "sn2.25:3.3"
msgid "Anicchā piṇḍamesanā, "
msgstr "Desireless they sought alms; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:3.4"
msgid "anicchā sayanāsanaṃ; "
msgstr "desireless they used their lodgings. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:3.5"
msgid "Loke aniccataṃ ñatvā, "
msgstr "Knowing that the world was impermanent "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:3.6"
msgid "dukkhassantaṃ akaṃsu te. "
msgstr "they made an end of suffering. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.142, sc4
msgctxt "sn2.25:4.1"
msgid "Dupposaṃ katvā attānaṃ, "
msgstr "But now they’ve made themselves hard to look after, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:4.2"
msgid "gāme gāmaṇikā viya; "
msgstr "like chiefs in a village. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:4.3"
msgid "Bhutvā bhutvā nipajjanti, "
msgstr "They eat and eat and then lie down, "

# NOTE: The comm interpretation of “infatuated”, followed by BB, is wrong. the point here is that they eat too much and fall asleep in houses, which is considered unbecoming conduct for a mendicant. Several Vinaya rules deal with related issues.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:4.4"
msgid "parāgāresu mucchitā. "
msgstr "unconscious in the homes of others. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn2.25:5.1"
msgid "Saṃghassa añjaliṃ katvā, "
msgstr "Having raised my joined palms to the Saṅgha, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: vadāmahaṃ → vandāmahaṃ (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn2.25:5.2"
msgid "idhekacce vadāmahaṃ; "
msgstr "I speak here only about certain people. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:5.3"
msgid "Apaviddhā anāthā te, "
msgstr "They’re rejects, with no protector, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: tatheva te → tatheva ca (bj)
msgctxt "sn2.25:5.4"
msgid "yathā petā tatheva te. "
msgstr "just like those who have passed away. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn2.25:6.1"
msgid "Ye kho pamattā viharanti, "
msgstr "I’m speaking about "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:6.2"
msgid "te me sandhāya bhāsitaṃ; "
msgstr "those who live negligently. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:6.3"
msgid "Ye appamattā viharanti, "
msgstr "To those who live diligently "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn2.25:6.4"
msgid "namo tesaṃ karomahan”ti. "
msgstr "I pay homage.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
